column5: Fishing west side of Red Lake this fall. I've fished the east and northeast a bit, but never the far west near Pipestone Bay, etc... We'll be targeting walleyes and northern.

I've fished Red Lake for over 15 years, all areas of the Lake. We go to where the fish are as they do move every year. It can be a long drive to the West end but it can be productive. Only fishing it will tell.
We have fished the West end for the past 11 years and love it. Never fished east. When will you be up there ?
The Red Lake Fall Walleye Classic (Labor Day) is often won fishing the west end
I'll be up there Aug 20 to 28 and again June 2020.
